      "content": "I can see how these feelings are consuming you, and it's okay to feel this way. But remember, your worth isn't defined by this one incident. You have a past full of accomplishments and relationships, and those won't just vanish because of this. It's okay to grieve and feel overwhelmed, but don't let it consume you. You can still find joy and purpose in life, even in the midst of this. And remember, it's okay to ask for help. You don't have to do this alone. And while it may feel like your past self is gone, you still have a chance to make new memories and grow from this experience. It's not easy, but it's possible.",
